4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT GENERALLY REVISING CULTURAL AND AESTHETIC
5 PROJECTS GRANTS; PROVIDING CRITERIA BY WHICH THE CULTURAL AND AESTHETIC PROJECTS
6 ADVISORY COMMITTEE SHALL PRIORITIZE APPLICATIONS FOR GRANTS; PROVIDING AN EXCEPTION
7 ON THE REQUIREMENT TO OBTAIN A FEDERAL SYSTEM FOR AWARD MANAGEMENT NUMBER; AND
8 AMENDING SECTION 22-2-302, MCA.”
9
10 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
11
12 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Prioritization of cultural and aesthetic projects grant awards --
13 criteria. After the cultural and aesthetic projects advisory committee provided for in 2-15-1521 has reviewed the
14 applications to ensure compliance and determine whether the application meets the committee's criteria for
15 funding, the committee shall rank the projects by two criteria as follows:
16 (1) the status of an applicant's previous grant awards, for which:
17 (a) first priority will be given to qualified applicants who have not previously received an award;
18 (b) second priority will be given to applicants who have received one grant award in the previous
19 three funding cycles;
20 (c) third priority will be given to applicants who have received two grant awards in the previous
21 three funding cycles; and
22 (d) fourth priority will be given to applicants who have received three grant awards in the previous
23 three funding cycles; and
24 (2) the size of an applicant's annual operating budget, for which:
25 (a) first priority will be given to applicants whose total annual operating budget is less than
26 $99,999;
27 (b) second priority will be given to applicants whose total annual operating budget ranges between
28 $100,000 and $249,999;
