1 (c) third priority will be given to applicants whose total annual operating budget ranges between
2 $250,000 and $499,999; and
3 (d) fourth priority will be given to applicants whose total annual operating budget is equal to or
4 greater than $500,000.
5 (3) Between each funding cycle, the committee, in consultation with the budget director, shall
6 increase the budget limits established in subsection (2) to account for inflation.
7
8 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Acquisition of federal system for award management number. Grant
9 applicants for a cultural or aesthetic project whose total program budget does not exceed $100,000 and who do
10 not receive or use federal funds to operate may request a waiver from the committee for the requirement to
11 obtain a federal system for award management number, or SAMs number, if complying with the requirement
12 would be burdensome. The committee may not unreasonably withhold the waiver.
13
14 Section 3. Section 22-2-302, MCA, is amended to read:
15 "22-2-302. Advisory committee -- powers and duties. (1) The Subject to [section 1], the cultural
16 and aesthetic projects advisory committee provided for in 2-15-1521 shall review all proposals for cultural and
17 aesthetic project grants before they are submitted to the legislature.
18 (2) Consistent with the rules adopted in accordance with 22-2-303, the committee shall make
19 recommendations to the legislature on each proposal submitted to the committee.
20 (3) The committee's recommendations to the legislature are advisory only.
21 (4) The committee shall present its recommendations to the appropriations committee of the
22 legislature by the 15th day of any regular legislative session."
23
24 NEW SECTION. Section 4. Codification instruction. [Sections 1 and 2] are intended to be codified
25 as an integral part of Title 22, chapter 2, part 3, and the provisions of Title 22, chapter 2, part 3, apply to
26 [sections 1 and 2].
